radiographic_examinations.findings: Partially imaged lower lungs are clear other than minimal bibasilar atelectasis. Liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation; no focal lesions or biliary dilatation. Normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands. Mildly dilated loops of terminal and distal ileum with fecalized material and mild wall hyperenhancement, concerning for early small bowel obstruction. Appendix visualized portions measure 5-6 mm with minimal fat stranding and fluid around it. Moderate free fluid in the pelvis.
